summary:
On personal level, I have high emotional intelligence and self-awareness which enable me to collaborate in the most efficient and effective way. I am capable to influence people without power and to offer an effective consultancy. I am curious, enthusiastic, persistence, assertive and decisive. I have sense of responsibility and willingness  to help others. 

On professional level, I enjoy working in a multidisciplinary environment with the opportunity to develop and acquire new skills and competences (soft and hard skills). This enable me to analyze and solve problems with a high drive for quality and performance improvement mindset. As a team member, I add value to my deliverables by means of my broad engineering skills, my proactive mindset and my motivation to get things done. I drive a culture of continuous improvement and maintains an effective and efficient Quality Management System in compliance to Customer Requirements Specifications. All of this enable me to be top performer.

profile_positions.description:
Mission:
To secure parts quality proactively by
• Having our design optimized by involving those who will manufacture it 
• securing the supplier manufacturing / qualification processes

Vision:
Map product specifications (TPD) to manufacturing process at supplier
•Validate part qualification process at supplier.
•Validate production process at supplier.

Activities:
• Supplier selection and scouting on Quality & Technology from a production perspective.
• Supplier performance management (Audit, Supplier Profile setting & tracking - QLTC).
• Influencing design for a predictable R4V conform QLTC specifications on industrialization (DfT, DfM, DfC, DfD) via Early Supplier Involvement and lessons learned.
• Create standard industrialization requirements for design.
• Create standardized NPI processes and test methodologies at supplier which allows smooth transition from design to volume production to fulfill time to market (Production Process Flow, Process FMEA, Value Stream Mapping, SPC, Production Verification.
• Part (re)allocation, Supplier reallocation via Product Family Team.
profile_positions.title: Supplier Quality Engineer Electronics

profile_positions.description:
• Document the Ordering Management System (OMS).
• Responsible to define the Standard Operation Procedures (SOP) and Warehouse Management System (WMS) IT tools, based on the OMS process defined by the WMS Architect.
• Responsible to use the IT tools:  Team Center, ASML-Q and SAP-ZECN as a Change Specialist & Manager in compliance to ASML QMS and Release & Configuration Manager in compliance to PInS QMS.
• Responsible of the Change Request Assessment Report (impact and risk analysis) as CCB member, in compliance to: PInS, ASML and customer QMS.
• Responsible of the Operational engineering deliverables defined in the OMS: Process documentation, SOP definition, IT tool work instructions definition.
profile_positions.title: Configuration and Release Manager

profile_positions.description:
• Participate in Corrective Action Preventive Actions (CAPA) Process like investigation and implementation as Validation & Verification engineer.
• Drive the strategy, approach and execution of the CAPA team to verify the implementations as proposed by the CAPA team to address the root cause of the problem within scope, in compliance to FDA Medical devices regulations.
profile_positions.title: Validation & Verification (V&V) Engineer

profile_positions.location: Kastanjelaan 400, Building SFH-2, 5616 LZ Eindhoven, The Netherlands
profile_positions.description:
•	Interim Project Leader and Proto Integrator for a Laser Module End of Line Tester.
•	Accountable for design and deliver safe, reliable and effective laser products to the market.
•	Responsible to comply with applicable Philips and external regulatory and compliance requirements (Functional & Customer Requirement Specifications).
•	Responsible for product and process release of Philips Photonics products, by means of Design and Manufacturing Process / Production Validation and Verification.
•	Work on multiple projects in an international environment.
•	Define, carry out and document release activities together with the development team and in-house and external parties.
•	Responsible for product release; reliability validation of new PPM products, component approval, design and release documentation, product appearance, failure analysis (FMEA), substances and material tests and certification (Product Safety and Environment compliance).
•	Responsible for process release; Serial production readiness, Process flow chart, Process capability, Gauge R&R, Control plan, Traceability, Test equipment and Process approval, 
•	Responsible for automotive compliance regulations; APQP and PPAP as TIER2.
•	Accountable for TPD engineering.
profile_positions.title: Quality & Compliance & Verfication Engineer

profile_positions.description:
o	Responsible to get and maintain the certification mark needed for Global Access. Market (GMA) for all Océ products: e.g. UL, CE, CCC, EAC, RCM, FCC, Energy Star
o	Certification Institutes contact person: e.g. UL, TUV (SUD-NORD), CQC, FDA, BG.
o	Mentoring Projects to comply with Machinery (MD), Low Voltage (LVD) and EMC directive for all business units of Océ in all designs phases and products life cycle.
o	Product Safety specialist-expert for IEC/UL 60950 and IEC/UL 62368.
o	Client Test Data Program Reviewer for UL (CTDP Program) and Testing at Manufacture’s Premises Reviewer for TUV-NORD (TMP (2) Program) CB scheme.
o	Author of GMA Océ internal standards, and key stakeholder of EMC, Mechanical and Electrical Safety Océ internal standard.
o	Making Risk Analysis and Risk Assessment to comply with LVD, MD needed to pass Océ milestones and required to validate the CE declaration for Océ products.
profile_positions.title: Product Safety and Environment Officer-Expert

profile_positions.location: De Run 6501, 5504 DR, Veldhoven, The Netherlands.
profile_positions.description:
• Operate in multidisciplinary team.
• Influence the definition and design on manufacturability, testability, reliability and EMC compliancy ( DFM=Design For Manufacturing,  DFT=Design For Testability, DFR=Design For Reliability, DFE=Design For EMC Compliancy, grounding & shielding concepts) 
• Specify and document the test requirements.
• Design and document the qualification tools for integration purpose.
• Execute measurements on test set-up or prototype machine and document results to ensure that the electrical architecture of the measurement systems meet the requirements.
• Execute and document EMC tests on subsystem level
• Interfacing with other electrical integration engineers.
• Make a work breakdown and a realistic integration plan for the complete integration of the electronics modules.
• Transfer knowledge to production and service engineers.
• Solving problems during full proto product integration.
• Support production and service as an expert (4th line support)
• Analyze and solve reliability issues  
• Act as a technical coach for colleagues.
• Knowledge on SEMI, CE, NFPA regulations
• Affinity/attention to the details of the designs made by others
